## OUR ART

[Allison Horst](https://allisonhorst.github.io/) creates original art for Openscapes. Formerly an artist in residence at NCEAS and Assistant Teaching Professor at the Bren School of Environmental Science & Management at the University of California, Santa Barbara, Allison now works as a Data Scientist Advocate at [Observable](https://observablehq.com/). She is also one of the inaugural Openscapes Champions. Allison has a background in the fine arts, and in recent years, began creating digital open artwork for data science and statistics education -- explore her [Openscapes gallery](gallery.qmd) and her [stats illustrations](https://allisonhorst.com/).

See all of Allison's Openscapes artwork on the [gallery page](gallery.qmd), including our logo, which represents open landscapes of possibility and the data within them.

